Nicholas Tooth, 25, was playing for the Quirindi Lions against the Narrabri Blue Boars in NSW on Saturday  . 
  He sustained a head injury when he hit his head on an opponent's shoulder in a tackle . 
  Mr Tooth was airlifted to Newcastle's John Hunter Hospital but died late on Sunday . 
  The young man was visiting his hometown for the weekend . 
  He was described by his club as a 'highly regarded' player . 
  Australian Rugby Union and NSW Rugby Union have offered their support . 
 